Why Worry Kills?<br/><br/>WHY WORRY KILLS?
<br /><br />Death was walking toward a city one morning and a man asked, &quot;What are you going to do?&quot; 
<br /><br />&quot;I'm going to take 100 people,&quot; Death replied. 
<br /><br />&quot;That's horrible!&quot; the man said. 
<br /><br />&quot;That's the way it is,&quot; Death said. &quot;That's what I do.&quot; 
<br /><br />The man hurried to warn everyone he could about Death's plan. 
<br /><br />As evening fell, he met Death again. &quot;You told me you were going to take 100 people,&quot; the man said. &quot;Why did 1,000 die?&quot; 
<br /><br />&quot;I kept my word,&quot; Death responded. &quot;I only took 100 people. Worry took the others.&quot; 
